Argentine Stocks: Banco Macro, Edenor, Grupo Galicia, Ledesma

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-04-04T21:13:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/argentine-stocks-banco-marco-grupo-financiero-galicia-ledesma.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4:00 p.m.  New York  time.  The Merval Index rose 1.2 percent to 3,513.34.  Empresa Distribuidora y Comercializadora Norte (EDN)  SA,
or Edenor, rose 2.6 percent to 2.34 pesos.  Standard & Poor’s 
affirmed its “B-” rating for the Argentine power distribution
company, with a “stable” outlook.  Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL)  ,  Argentina ’s largest
consumer lender, rose 3.9 percent to 5.83 pesos. Argentine
sovereign bond prices advanced today, which signals higher
values for banks’ fixed income holdings.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)  , Argentina’s largest lender by market value, rose 3.2
percent to 17.95 pesos, its steepest increase in seven weeks.  Ledesma SAAI (LEDE AF), the Argentine sugar company, rose
1.3 percent to 9.95 pesos, its highest price in eight weeks.
Sugar prices climbed in New York on supply concerns in  Brazil 
after heavy rains stalled harvests.  To contact the reporter on this story:
